2.1 mm
</quantity>
(male, female), but the above samples ranging between 13 and 
<quantity box="[610,691,1420,1445]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
in length, and 1.8 and 
<quantity box="[959,1047,1420,1444]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
in width; metazonite to prozonite width ratio &lt;1.6 (
<figureCitation box="[367,502,1455,1480]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,249,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,306,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,303,1685]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Brachydesmus pigmentatus Attems, 1951, males from Hyrcan Nature Reserve, Azerbaijan. A: habitus, entire body, dorsal view. B: anterior part of body, dorsal view. C: right half of metatergite 10, dorsal view. D: posterior part of body, dorsal view. E: gonopods in situ, ventral view. F: right gonopod, mesal view. Designations: en, endomere; ex, exomere; k, spine at base of endomere; t, tooth near base of femorite. Pictures A and E by K. Makarov, taken not to scale. Line drawings B – D by S. Dashdamirov, scale bar: 1.0 mm (B – D), 0.3 mm (F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052397/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 8 
<emphasis box="[437,454,1456,1479]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[454,468,1455,1480]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">–</emphasis>
8 
<emphasis box="[482,502,1457,1480]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">D</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Live coloration usually uniformly grey-brown to brown, in alcohol sometimes faded to light brown (
<figureCitation box="[394,477,1492,1517]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,249,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,306,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,303,1685]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Brachydesmus pigmentatus Attems, 1951, males from Hyrcan Nature Reserve, Azerbaijan. A: habitus, entire body, dorsal view. B: anterior part of body, dorsal view. C: right half of metatergite 10, dorsal view. D: posterior part of body, dorsal view. E: gonopods in situ, ventral view. F: right gonopod, mesal view. Designations: en, endomere; ex, exomere; k, spine at base of endomere; t, tooth near base of femorite. Pictures A and E by K. Makarov, taken not to scale. Line drawings B – D by S. Dashdamirov, scale bar: 1.0 mm (B – D), 0.3 mm (F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052397/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 8 
<emphasis box="[460,477,1492,1515]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,807,2021]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
All characters as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lohmander" authorityYear="1936" box="[420,548,1527,1552]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assimilis">
<emphasis box="[420,548,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">B. assimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[563,630,1527,1552]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,249,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,306,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,303,1685]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Brachydesmus pigmentatus Attems, 1951, males from Hyrcan Nature Reserve, Azerbaijan. A: habitus, entire body, dorsal view. B: anterior part of body, dorsal view. C: right half of metatergite 10, dorsal view. D: posterior part of body, dorsal view. E: gonopods in situ, ventral view. F: right gonopod, mesal view. Designations: en, endomere; ex, exomere; k, spine at base of endomere; t, tooth near base of femorite. Pictures A and E by K. Makarov, taken not to scale. Line drawings B – D by S. Dashdamirov, scale bar: 1.0 mm (B – D), 0.3 mm (F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052397/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), except as follows. Paraterga subhorizontal to poorly declivous, mostly only slightly rounded laterally; caudolateral corner obtuse-angled only until segment 6, pointed or nearly pointed and increasingly well drawn behind rear tergal margin starting with segment 8 or 9 (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1236,1599,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,249,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,306,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,303,1685]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Brachydesmus pigmentatus Attems, 1951, males from Hyrcan Nature Reserve, Azerbaijan. A: habitus, entire body, dorsal view. B: anterior part of body, dorsal view. C: right half of metatergite 10, dorsal view. D: posterior part of body, dorsal view. E: gonopods in situ, ventral view. F: right gonopod, mesal view. Designations: en, endomere; ex, exomere; k, spine at base of endomere; t, tooth near base of femorite. Pictures A and E by K. Makarov, taken not to scale. Line drawings B – D by S. Dashdamirov, scale bar: 1.0 mm (B – D), 0.3 mm (F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052397/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 8A 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1185,1199,1599,1624]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">–</emphasis>
8D
</figureCitation>
). Fore margins of paraterga mostly straight, anterolateral corner usually angular. Tergal setae a little longer, largely pointed. Male prefemora strongly bulging laterad. Gonopod (
<figureCitation box="[682,813,1671,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="16.[151,249,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,306,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,303,1685]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 8. Brachydesmus pigmentatus Attems, 1951, males from Hyrcan Nature Reserve, Azerbaijan. A: habitus, entire body, dorsal view. B: anterior part of body, dorsal view. C: right half of metatergite 10, dorsal view. D: posterior part of body, dorsal view. E: gonopods in situ, ventral view. F: right gonopod, mesal view. Designations: en, endomere; ex, exomere; k, spine at base of endomere; t, tooth near base of femorite. Pictures A and E by K. Makarov, taken not to scale. Line drawings B – D by S. Dashdamirov, scale bar: 1.0 mm (B – D), 0.3 mm (F)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052397/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 8E, 8F</figureCitation>
) subfalcate, bipartite, with a long, very simple, fingershaped, ventrad only slightly and regularly curved, apically acuminate exomere (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1073,1100,1708,1733]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">ex</emphasis>
), this being tightly appressed ventrally to a similar, also finger-shaped, but somewhat shorter endomere (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1000,1028,1743,1768]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">en</emphasis>
), the latter at base carrying a small, medioventral spine (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[394,409,1780,1805]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">k</emphasis>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[440,468,1780,1805]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">en</emphasis>
representing a solenomere devoid of a hairy pulvillus; a small tooth (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1323,1332,1780,1805]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">t</emphasis>
) located medioventrally at base of femorite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,807,2021]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1852,1877]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has hitherto been considered as subendemic to Hyrcania within N and NW 
<collectingCountry box="[1323,1368,1853,1876]" name="Iran" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Iran</collectingCountry>
alone (
<collectingRegion box="[158,233,1887,1912]" country="Iran" name="Alborz" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Elburs</collectingRegion>
and Zagros mountains) (
<bibRefCitation author="Attems" box="[518,668,1887,1912]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Attems, C. (1951) Ergebnisse der Osterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1949 / 50. Myriopoden vom Iran gesammelt von der Expedition Hainz Loffler und Genossen 1949 / 50. Sitzungsberichte der Osterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch-naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, Abt. I, 160, 387 - 426." type="journal article" year="1951">Attems 1951</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch" box="[681,879,1887,1912]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1981 b) Diplopoda from Iran (Glomeridae, Glomeridellidae, Platydesmidae, Polydesmidae). Senckenbergiana biologica, 61 (5 / 6), 421 - 427." type="journal article" year="1981" yearSuffix="b">Golovatch 1981b</bibRefCitation>
). The above records are thus new to the fauna of the 
<collectingCountry box="[192,457,1924,1949]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Republic of 
<collectingRegion box="[331,457,1924,1949]" country="Iran" name="Azarbayjan-e Sharqi" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Azerbaijan</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
, in general also to that of the Caucasus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,807,2021]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Given such a considerable range of variation in body size in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1951" box="[903,1073,1961,1984]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pigmentatus">
<emphasis box="[903,1073,1961,1984]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">B. pigmentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we do not hesitate to formally synonymize here this species with 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch, 1976" authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1976" box="[556,883,1996,2021]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pereliae">
<emphasis box="[556,681,1996,2021]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">B. pereliae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch" box="[691,883,1996,2021]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1976) [New species of polydesmidans (Polydesmida, Diplopoda) of the USSR]. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 55 (10), 1567 - 1570. [in Russian, English abstract]" type="journal article" year="1976">Golovatch, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the latter taxon known from the W Kopetdagh Mountains, SW 
<collectingCountry box="[335,493,151,176]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
. Indeed, the 
<typeStatus box="[638,736,151,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1976" box="[774,897,151,176]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pereliae">
<emphasis box="[774,897,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. pereliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was said to be 
<quantity box="[1073,1153,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1266,1367,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.17" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="1.17">1.17 mm</quantity>
wide, whereas the gonopods of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1951" box="[444,614,189,212]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pigmentatus">
<emphasis box="[444,614,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. pigmentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1976" box="[672,795,188,213]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pereliae">
<emphasis box="[672,795,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. pereliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been noted as being virtually identical (
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1976) [New species of polydesmidans (Polydesmida, Diplopoda) of the USSR]. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 55 (10), 1567 - 1570. [in Russian, English abstract]" type="journal article" year="1976">Golovatch 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Hence the new synonymy advanced: 
<taxonomicName authority="Attems, 1951" authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1951" box="[648,973,223,248]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pigmentatus">
<emphasis box="[648,816,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. pigmentatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Attems" box="[823,973,223,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Attems, C. (1951) Ergebnisse der Osterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1949 / 50. Myriopoden vom Iran gesammelt von der Expedition Hainz Loffler und Genossen 1949 / 50. Sitzungsberichte der Osterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch-naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, Abt. I, 160, 387 - 426." type="journal article" year="1951">Attems, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="Golovatch, 1976" authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1976" box="[1003,1322,223,248]" class="Diplopoda" family="Polydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pereliae" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis box="[1003,1125,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. pereliae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch" box="[1132,1322,223,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Golovatch, S. I. (1976) [New species of polydesmidans (Polydesmida, Diplopoda) of the USSR]. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 55 (10), 1567 - 1570. [in Russian, English abstract]" type="journal article" year="1976">Golovatch, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1333,1407,224,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
